narrativity.rewrite:
I was lying in bed at 3pm on a Tuesday, doom-scrolling through my phone, when my friend texted me to just go for a walk. I rolled my eyes so hard. Here we go again, I thought — another person about to hit me with that motivational gym-bro shit about exercise fixing everything. I wanted to tell them to fuck off.

But I went anyway. Came back 20 minutes later feeling... different. Lighter somehow.

So yeah, fuck every smug cunt who says working out is a key component to mental health and if you just get moving you're a lot of the way to feeling better. Fuck them especially because — and I hate admitting this — they're actually right -_-;;;;
